    • Method Detail

      • comesBefore

        public boolean comesBefore(T[] x,
                  int a,
                  int b)
        Compare two elements in the given array. This determines the order of the elements in the sorted array.

        The default implementation returns true if x[a].compareTo(x[b]) < 0, which sorts the array into the elements' natural ordering. A subclass can override this method to obtain a different ordering criterion.

        Specified by:
        comesBefore in class Sorting.Object<T>
        Parameters:
        x - Array being sorted.
        a - Index of first array element being compared.
        b - Index of second array element being compared.
        Returns:
        True if x[a] comes before x[b] in the desired ordering, false otherwise.
